This paper is about optimizing hyperparameters for deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on using derivative-free optimization methods, which are often used in the field of numerical optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses image data sets (MNIST and CIFAR-10), which suggests a possible sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of categorical variables, which could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
